{"id":"1609.08983","submitter":"Tao Jiang","authors":"Tao Jiang, Yuejian Peng, Biao Wu","title":"Turan numbers of extensions of some sparse hypergraphs via Lagrangians","comments":"21 pages","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.CO","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  Given a positive integer $n$ and an $r$-uniform hypergraph (or $r$-graph for\nshort) $F$, the Turan number $ex(n,F)$ of $F$ is the maximum number of edges in\nan $r$-graph on $n$ vertices that does not contain $F$ as a subgraph. The\nextension $H^F $ of $F$ is obtained as follows: For each pair of vertices\n$v_i,v_j$ in $F$ not contained in an edge of $F$, we add a set $B_{ij}$ of\n$r-2$ new vertices and the edge $\\{v_i,v_j\\} \\cup B_{ij}$, where the $B_{ij}$\n's are pairwise disjoint over all such pairs $\\{i,j\\}$. Let $K^r_p$ denote the\ncomplete $r$-graph on $p$ vertices. For all sufficiently large $n$, we\ndetermine the Turan numbers of the extensions of a $3$-uniform $t$-matching, a\n$3$-uniform linear star of size $t$, and a $4$-uniform linear star of size $t$,\nrespectively. We also show that the unique extremal hypergraphs are balanced\nblowups of $K^3_{3t-1}, K^3_{2t}$, and $K^4_{3t}$, respectively. Our results\ngeneralize the recent result of Hefetz and Keevash [7].\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 28 Sep 2016 16:06:40 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-09-29"}
