6}\\ L_\\odot$ require low\naccretion rates and starting entropy, and that the temperature of the accreting\nmaterial is maintained close to the nebula temperature. If instead the\ntemperature is near the value required to radiate the accretion luminosity,\n$4\\pi R^2\\sigma T_0^4\\sim (GM\\dot M/R)$, as suggested by previous work on\nradiative shocks in the context of star formation, gas giant planets form in a\nhot start with $L\\sim 10^{-4}\\ L_\\odot$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 28 Sep 2016 21:40:14 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 18 Nov 2016 21:38:12 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 6 Dec 2016 20:38:42 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-01-11"}
