his case, the monotone L\\'evy noise has the\nrepresentation\n$\\omega(t)=\\partial_t^\\dag+\\lambda\\partial_t^\\dag\\partial_t+\\partial_t+\\eta\\partial_t^\\dag\\partial_t\\partial_t$.\nHere, $\\partial_t^\\dag$ and $\\partial_t$ are the (formal) creation and\nannihilation operators at $t\\in\\mathbb R_+$ acting in $\\mathbb F$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 29 Sep 2016 09:04:22 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-09-30"}
